{"title_page": "2018\u201319 Toronto Maple Leafs season", "text_new": "{{NHLTeamSeason\n| Season = 2018\u201319\n| year = 2018\n| Team = Toronto Maple Leafs\n| League = NHL\n| Division = [[Atlantic Division (NHL)|Atlantic]]\n| DivisionRank = 3rd\n| Conference = [[Eastern Conference (NHL)|Eastern]]\n| ConferenceRank = 5th\n| Record = 46\u201328\u20138\n| HomeRecord = 23\u201316\u20132\n| RoadRecord = 23\u201312\u20136\n| GoalsFor = 286\n| GoalsAgainst = 251\n| GeneralManager = [[Kyle Dubas]]\n| Coach = [[Mike Babcock]]\n| Captain = ''Vacant''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nhl.com/news/john-tavares-named-toronto-maple-leafs-alternate-captain/c-300090868|title=Tavares named one of three Maple Leafs alternate captains|publisher=NHL.com|date=September 13, 2018|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref>\n| AltCaptain = [[Patrick Marleau]]<br />[[Morgan Rielly]]<br />[[John Tavares]]\n| Arena = [[Scotiabank Arena]]\n| Attendance = \n| MinorLeague = [[Toronto Marlies]] ([[American Hockey League|AHL]])<br />[[Newfoundland Growlers]] ([[ECHL]])\n| GoalsLeader = [[John Tavares]] (47)\n| AssistsLeader = [[Mitch Marner]] (68)\n| PointsLeader = Mitch Marner (94)\n| PlusMinusLeader = [[Ron Hainsey]] (+30)\n| PIMLeader = [[Zach Hyman]] (65)\n| WinsLeader = [[Frederik Andersen]] (36)\n| GAALeader = Frederik Andersen (2.77)\n| DivisionWin = \n| PresidentsTrophy = \n| ConferenceWin = \n| StanleyCup = \n}}\nThe '''2018\u201319 Toronto Maple Leafs season''' was the [[List of Toronto Maple Leafs seasons|102nd season]] for the [[National Hockey League]] franchise that was established on November 22, 1917.<ref>{{cite book |last=National Hockey League|title=The National Hockey League Official Guide & Record Book/2011|year=2010 |publisher= Triumph Books |page= 123|isbn= 978-1-60078-422-4}}</ref> The [[Toronto Maple Leafs|Maple Leafs]] forward group changed significantly before the season, losing team veterans [[Tyler Bozak]], [[James van Riemsdyk]] and [[Leo Komarov]] while adding all-star centre [[John Tavares]] in free agency, which many publications called one of the biggest signings in NHL history.<ref>{{cite web |title=John Tavares hits unrestricted free agency as midnight deadline passes |url=https://www.sportsnet.ca/hockey/nhl/john-tavares-hits-free-agency-midnight-deadline-passes/ |website=Roger's Sportsnet |accessdate=August 19, 2018 |date=July 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Tavares could become one of most desirable free agents in NHL history |url=https://www.nhl.com/news/john-tavares-one-of-the-most-desirable-free-agents-in-nhl-history/c-299092454 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=August 19, 2018 |date=June 18, 2018}}</ref> On April 1, 2019, the Maple Leafs clinched a playoff spot after a 2\u20131 win over the [[2018\u201319 New York Islanders season|New York Islanders]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Compton |first1=Brian |title=Maple Leafs clinch playoff berth with victory against Islanders |url=https://www.nhl.com/news/toronto-maple-leafs-new-york-islanders-game-recap/c-306351586 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=April 2, 2019 |date=April 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe Maple Leafs faced the [[2018\u201319 Boston Bruins season|Boston Bruins]] in the first round of the playoffs for the second straight year, where they lost in seven games.\n\n==Standings==\n{{2018\u201319 NHL Atlantic Division standings|team=TOR}}\n\n==Record vs opponents==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"10\"|Eastern Conference\n!colspan=\"6\"|Western Conference\n|-\n!colspan=\"5\"|Atlantic Division\n!colspan=\"5\"|Metropolitan Division\n!colspan=\"3\"|Central Division\n!colspan=\"3\"|Pacific Division\n|-\n!colspan=\"1\" width=100|Team\n!colspan=\"2\" width=100|Home\n!colspan=\"2\" width=100|Road\n!colspan=\"1\" width=100|Team\n!colspan=\"2\" width=100|Home\n!colspan=\"2\" width=100|Road\n!colspan=\"1\" width=100|Team\n!colspan=\"1\" width=50|Home\n!colspan=\"1\" width=50|Road\n!colspan=\"1\" width=100|Team\n!colspan=\"1\" width=50|Home\n!colspan=\"1\" width=5