|01}} || [[Yegor Korshkov]] || 2-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Maple Leafs Sign Egor Korshkov to Entry Level Contract |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/leafs-sign-korshkov-to-entry-level-contract/c-307140196 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=May 2, 2019 |date=May 1, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Draft picks==\n{{See also|List of Toronto Maple Leafs draft picks}}\nBelow are the Toronto Maple Leafs' selections at the [[2018 NHL Entry Draft]], which was held on June 22 and 23, 2018, at the [[American Airlines Center]] in [[Dallas, Texas]]. The Leafs drafted a total of nine players. They held on to only three (rounds 4, 5, 7) of their own seven picks. On the first day of the draft they exchanged their first-round pick for a lower first-round pick held by the [[St. Louis Blues]] but did receive the Blues' third-round pick as well, their second round pick had been traded to the [[Montreal Canadiens]] in the [[Tom\u00e1\u0161 Plekanec|Tomas Plekanec]] deal in February 2018, their third-round pick was given to the [[New Jersey Devils]] as compensation for signing general manager [[Lou Lamoriello]] in 2015, and their sixth-round pick had been traded to the [[Vegas Golden Knights]] in the [[Calvin Pickard]] deal in October 2017. Through various trades they acquired an additional six picks, including the first-round pick originally held by St. Louis mentioned above.\n<!-- Please do not forget to add reliable sources when listing any possible high-profile prospects -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-\n! Round\n! #\n! Player\n! Pos\n! Nationality\n! College/Junior/Club Team (League)\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|29<sup>1</sup>\n| [[Rasmus Sandin]]\n| D\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} Sweden\n| [[Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds]] ([[Ontario Hockey League|OHL]])\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|52<sup>2</sup>\n| [[Sean Durzi]]\n| D\n| {{flagicon|Canada}} Canada\n| [[Owen Sound Attack]] (OHL)\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|76<sup>3</sup>\n| [[Semyon Der-Arguchintsev]]\n| C\n| {{flagicon|Russia}} Russia\n| [[Peterborough Petes]] (OHL)\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|83<sup>4</sup>\n| [[Riley Stotts]]\n| C\n| {{flagicon|Canada}} Canada\n| [[Calgary Hitmen]] ([[Western Hockey League|WHL]])\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|4\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|118\n| [[Mac Hollowell]]\n| D\n| {{flagicon|Canada}} Canada\n| [[Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds]] (OHL)\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|149\n| [[Filip Kr\u00e1l|Filip Kral]]\n| D\n| {{flagicon|Czech Republic}} Czech Republic\n| [[Spokane Chiefs]] (WHL)\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|156<sup>5</sup>\n| [[Pontus Holmberg]]\n| RW\n| {{flagicon|Sweden}} Sweden\n| [[VIK V\u00e4ster\u00e5s HK]] ([[Hockeyettan]])\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|7\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|209<sup>6</sup>\n| [[Zachary Bouthillier]]\n| G\n| {{flagicon|Canada}} Canada\n| [[Chicoutimi Saguen\u00e9ens]] ([[Quebec Major Junior Hockey League|QMJHL]])\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|7\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|211\n| [[Semyon Kizimov]]\n| RW\n| {{flagicon|Russia}} Russia\n| [[HC Ladia Togliatti|Ladia Togliatti]] ([[Junior Hockey League (Russia)|MHL]])\n|}\n'''Notes:'''\n# The [[Winnipeg Jets]]' first-round pick went to the Toronto Maple Leafs as the result of a trade on June 22, 2018, that sent a first-round pick in 2018 (25th overall) to St. Louis in exchange for a third-round pick in 2018 (76th overall) and this pick.<ref name=\"Bluesup4withLeafs\">{{cite web|title=Leafs select D Sandin with No. 29 pick|url=https://www.tsn.ca/leafs-select-d-sandin-with-no-29-pick-1.1120978|date=June 22, 2018|accessdate=June 22, 2018}}</ref>\n# The [[San Jose Sharks]]' second-round pick went to the Toronto Maple Leafs as the result of a trade on February 22, 2016, that sent [[Roman Pol\u00e1k|Roman Polak]] and [[Nick Spaling]] to San Jose in exchange for [[Raffi Torres]], a second-round pick in [[2017 NHL Entry Draft|2017]] and this pick.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sharks acquire Polak, Spaling from Maple Leafs |url=https://www.nhl.com/news/roman-polak-nick-spaling-traded-to-san-jose-sharks-by-toronto-maple-leafs/c-279061788 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=June 20, 2018 |date=February 22, 2016}}</ref>\n# The [[St. Louis Blues]]' third-round pick went the Toronto Maple Leafs as the result of a trade on June 22, 2018, that sent a first-round pick in 2018 (25th overall) to St. Louis in exchange for Winnipeg's first-round pick in 2018 (29th overall) and this pick.<ref name=\"Bluesup4withLeafs\" />\n# The [[San Jose Sharks]]' third-round pick went to the Toronto Maple Leafs as the result of a trade on February 27, 2016, that sent [[James Reimer (ice hockey)|James Reimer]] and [[Jeremy Morin]] to San Jose in exchange for [[Alex Stalock]], [[Ben Smith (ice hockey, born 1988)|Ben Smith]] and this pick (being conditional at the time of the trade).<ref>{{cite web |last1=Basu |first1=Arpon |title=Reimer traded to Sharks by Maple Leafs |url=https://www.nhl.com/news/james-reimer-traded-to-sharks-by-maple-leafs/c-279192062 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=June 20, 2018 |date=February 27, 2016}}</ref>\n# The [[Buffalo Sabres]]' sixth-round pick went to the Toronto Maple Leafs as the result of a trade on June 23, 2018, that sent Toronto's sixth-round pick in [[2019 NHL Entry Draft|2019]] to Buffalo in exchange for this pick.\n# The [[Anaheim Ducks]]' seventh-round pick went to the Toronto Maple Leafs as the result of a trade January 10, 2017, that sent [[Jhonas Enroth]] to Anaheim in exchange for this pick.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Seravalli |first1=Frank |title=Ducks acquire G Enroth from Maple Leafs |url=https://www.tsn.ca/ducks-aquire-g-enroth-from-maple-leafs-1.647840 |website=TSN |accessdate=June 20, 2018 |date=January 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Toronto Maple Leafs}}\n{{Toronto Maple Leafs seasons}}\n{{2018\u201319 NHL season by team}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2018-19 Toronto Maple Leafs season}}\n[[Category:Toronto Maple Leafs seasons]]\n[[Category:2018\u201319 NHL season by team|Toronto Maple Leafs]]\n[[Category:2018\u201319 in Canadian ice hockey by team|Maple Leafs]]\n[[Category:2018 in Toronto]]\n[[Category:2019 in Toronto]]\n", "text_old": "{{NHLTeamSeason\n| Season = 2018\u201319\n| year = 2018\n| Team = Toronto Maple Leafs\n| League = NHL\n| Division = [[Atlantic Division (NHL)|Atlantic]]\n| DivisionRank = 3rd\n| Conference = [[Eastern Conference (NHL)|Eastern]]\n| ConferenceRank = 5th\n| Record = 46\u201328\u20138\n| HomeRecord = 23\u201316\u20132\n| RoadRecord = 23\u201312\u20136\n| GoalsFor = 286\n| GoalsAgainst = 251\n| GeneralManager = [[Kyle Dubas]]\n| Coach = [[Mike Babcock]]\n| Captain = ''Vacant''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nhl.com/news/john-tavares-named-toronto-maple-leafs-alternate-captain/c-300090868|title=Tavares named one of three Maple Leafs alternate captains|publisher=NHL.com|date=September 13, 2018|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref>\n| AltCaptain = [[Patrick Marleau]]<br />[[Morgan Rielly]]<br />[[John Tavares]]\n| Arena = [[Scotiabank Arena]]\n| Attendance = \n| MinorLeague = [[Toronto Marlies]] ([[American Hockey League|AHL]])<br />[[Newfoundland Growlers]] ([[ECHL]])\n| GoalsLeader = [[John Tavares]] (47)\n| AssistsLeader = [[Mitch Marner]] (68)\n| PointsLeader = Mitch Marner (94)\n| PlusMinusLeader = [[Ron Hainsey]] (+30)\n| PIMLeader = [[Zach Hyman]] (65)\n| WinsLeader = [[Frederik Andersen]] (36)\n| GAALeader = Frederik Andersen (2.77)\n| DivisionWin = \n| PresidentsTrophy = \n| ConferenceWin = \n| StanleyCup = \n}}\nThe '''2018\u201319 Toronto Maple Leafs season''' was the [[List of Toronto Maple Leafs seasons|102nd season]] for the [[National Hockey League]] franchise that was established on November 22, 1917.<ref>{{cite book |last=National Hockey League|title=The National Hockey League Official Guide & Record Book/2011|year=2010 |publisher= Triumph Books |page= 123|isbn= 978-1-60078-422-4}}</ref> The [[Toronto Maple Leafs|Maple Leafs]] forward group changed significantly before the season, losing team veterans [[Tyler Bozak]], [[James van Riemsdyk]] and [[Leo Komarov]] while adding all-star centre [[John Tavares]] in free agency, which many publications called one of the biggest signings in NHL history.<ref>{{cite web |title=John Tavares hits unrestricted free agency as midnight deadline passes |url=https://www.sportsnet.ca/hockey/nhl/john-tavares-hits-free-agency-midnight-deadline-passes/ |website=Roger's Sportsnet |accessdate=August 19, 2018 |date=July 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Tavares could become one of most desirable free agents in NHL history |url=https://www.nhl.com/news/john-tavares-one-of-the-most-desirable-free-agents-in-nhl-history/c-299092454 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=August 19, 2018 |date=June 18, 2018}}</ref> On April 1, 2019, the Maple Leafs clinched a playoff spot after a 2\u20131 win over the [[2018\u201319 New York Islanders season|New York Islanders]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Compton |first1=Brian |title=Maple Leafs clinch playoff berth with victory against Islanders |url=https://www.nhl.com/news/toronto-maple-leafs-new-york-islanders-game-recap/c-306351586 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=April 2, 2019 |date=April 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe Maple Leafs faced the [[2018\u201319 Boston Bruins season|Boston Bruins]] in the first round of the playoffs for the second straight year, where they lost in seven games.\n\n==Standings==\n{{2018\u201319 NHL Atlantic Division standings|team=TOR}}\n\n==Record vs opponents==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"10\"|Eastern Conference\n!colspan=\"6\"|Western Conference\n|-\n!colspan=\"5\"|Atlantic Division\n!colspan=\"5\"|Metropolitan Division\n!colspan=\"3\"|Central Division\n!colspan=\"3\"|Pacific Division\n|-\n!colspan=\"1\" width=100|Team\n!colspan=\"2\" width=100|Home\n!colspan=\"2\" width=100|Road\n!colspan=\"1\" width=100|Team\n!colspan=\"2\" width=100|Home\n!colspan=\"2\" width=100|Road\n!colspan=\"1\" width=100|Team\n!colspan=\"1\" width=50|Home\n!colspan=\"1\" width=50|Road\n!colspan=\"1\" width=100|Team\n!colspan=\"1\" width=50|Home\n!colspan=\"1\" width=50|Road\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Boston Bruins season|Boston]]\n| style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 4\u20132 || style=\"background:#fcc;\"| 2\u20133\n| style=\"background:#fcc;\"| 1\u20135 || style=\"background:#fcc;\"| 3\u20136\n||[[2018\u201319 Carolina Hurricanes season|Carolina]]\n| style=\"background:#fcc;\"| 1\u20134 ||\n| style=\"background:#fcc;\"| 2\u20135 || style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 4\u20131\n|[[2018\u201319 Chicago Blackhawks season|Chicago]]\n| style=\"background:#fcc;\"| 4\u20135\n| style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 7\u20136 {{ref|1|OT}}\n|[[2018\u201319 Anaheim Ducks season|Anaheim]]\n| style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 6\u20131\n| style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 2\u20131 {{ref|1|OT}}\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Buffalo Sabres season|Buffalo]]\n| style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 5\u20133 || style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 5\u20132\n| style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 4\u20133 {{ref|1|OT}} || style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 4\u20132\n|[[2018\u201319 Columbus Blue Jackets season|Columbus]]\n| style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 4\u20132 ||\n| style=\"background:#fcc;\"| 2\u20134 || style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 4\u20132\n|[[2018\u201319 Colorado Avalanche season|Colorado]]\n| style=\"background:#fcc;\"| 3\u20136\n| style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 5\u20132\n|[[2018\u201319 Arizona Coyotes season|Arizona]]\n| style=\"background:#fcc;\"| 2\u20134\n| style=\"background:#fcc;\"| 0\u20132\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Detroit Red Wings season|Detroit]]\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| 4\u20135 {{ref|1|OT}} || style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 5\u20134 {{ref|1|OT}}\n| style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 5\u20133 || style=\"background:#ffc;\"| 2\u20133 {{ref|1|OT}}\n|[[2018\u201319 New Jersey Devils season|New Jersey]]\n| style=\"background:#cfc;\"| 6\u2