ar || <ref>{{cite web |title=Maple Leafs Sign Rasmus Sandin to Entry-Level Contract |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/sandin-signs-entry-level-contract-with-maple-leafs/c-299497890 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=August 22, 2018 |date=July 15, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{start date|2018|09|21}} || [[Semyon Der-Arguchintsev]] || 3-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Maple Leafs Sign Semyon Der-Arguchintsev |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/leafs-sign-semyon-der-arguchintsev/c-300316178 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=September 25, 2018 |date=September 21, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{start date|2018|12|01}} || [[William Nylander]] || 6-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Maple Leafs Agree to Terms With William Nylander |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/leafs-agree-to-terms-with-nylander/c-302501362 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=December 1, 2018 |date=December 1, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Proteau |first1=Adam |title=Leafs Sign Nylander To Long Term Deal |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/leafs-sign-nylander-to-long-term-deal/c-302507748 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=December 3, 2018 |date=December 2, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{start date|2018|12|10}} || [[Calle Ros\u00e9n|Calle Rosen]] || 2-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Maple Leafs Sign Calle Rosen to Two-Year Contract Extension |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/calle-rosen-signs-extension-with-maple-leafs/c-302795918 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=December 11, 2018 |date=December 10, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{start date|2018|12|14}} || [[Ian Scott (ice hockey)|Ian Scott]] || 3-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Maple Leafs Sign Ian Scott to Entry-Level Contract |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/leafs-sign-scott/c-302927536 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=December 15, 2018 |date=December 14, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{start date|2019|01|13}} || [[Trevor Moore (ice hockey)|Trevor Moore]] || 2-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Leafs sign Moore to two-year contract extension |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/maple-leafs-sign-trevor-moore-to-contract-extension/c-303852022 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=January 13, 2019 |date=January 13, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{start date|2019|02|05}} || [[Auston Matthews]] || 5-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Leafs Agree to Terms with Auston Matthews on 5-Year Contract Extension |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/maple-leafs-auston-matthews-contract-extension/c-304500460 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=February 8, 2019 |date=February 5, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{start date|2019|03|05}} || [[Garret Sparks]] || 1-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Maple Leafs Sign Sparks to One-Year Extension |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/maple-leafs-sign-sparks-to-one-year-extension/c-305480542 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=March 6, 2019 |date=March 5, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{start date|2019|03|06}} || [[Andreas Borgman]] || 1-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Maple Leafs Sign Borgman to One-Year Extension |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/leafs-sign-borgman-to-extension/c-305522684 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=March 6, 2019 |date=March 6, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{start date|2019|03|07}} || [[Mac Hollowell]] || 3-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Maple Leafs Sign Mac Hollowell to Future Entry-Level Contract |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/leafs-sign-hollowell-to-future-elc/c-305551096 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=March 8, 2019 |date=March 7, 2019}}</ref>\n|- \n| {{start date|2019|03|13}} || [[Joseph Duszak]] || 2-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Maple Leafs Sign Joseph Duszak to Future Entry-Level Contract |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/leafs-sign-duszak-to-future-elc/c-305742300 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=March 15, 2019 |date=March 13, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{start date|2019|03|21}} || [[Nic Petan]] || 2-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Maple Leafs Sign Nic Petan to Two-Year Extension |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/leafs-sign-petan-to-extension/c-305996526 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |date=March 21, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{start date|2019|03|24}} || [[Joseph Woll]] || 3-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Maple Leafs Sign Joseph Woll to Entry-Level Contract |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/leafs-sign-woll-to-elc/c-306098368 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=March 25, 2019 |date=March 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{start date|2019|05|01}} || [[Yegor Korshkov]] || 2-year || <ref>{{cite web |title=Maple Leafs Sign Egor Korshkov to Entry Level Contract |url=https://www.nhl.com/mapleleafs/news/leafs-sign-korshkov-to-entry-level-contract/c-307140196 |website=NHL.com |accessdate=May 2, 2019 |date=May 1, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Draft picks==\n{{See also|List of Toronto Maple Leafs draft picks}}\nBelow are the Toronto Maple Leafs' selections at the [[2018 NHL Entry Draft]], which was held on June 22 and 23, 2018, at the [[American Airlines Center]] in [[Dallas, Texas]]. The Leafs drafted a total of nine players. They held on to only three (rounds 4, 5, 7) of their own seven picks. On the first day of the draft they exchanged their first-round pick for a lower first-round pick held by the [[St. Louis Blues]] but did receive the Blues' third-round pick as well, their second round pick had been traded to the [[Montreal Canadiens]] in the [[Tom\u00e1\u0161 Plekanec|Tomas Plekanec]] deal in February 2018, their third-round pick was given to the [[New Jersey Devils]] as compensation for signing general manager [[Lou Lamoriello]] in 2015, and their sixth-round pick had been traded to the [[Vegas Golden Knights]] in the [[Calvin Pickard]] deal in October 2017. Through various trades they acquired an additional six picks, including the first-round pick originally held by St. Louis mentioned above.\n<!-- Please do not forget to add reliable sources when listing any possible high-profile prospects -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-\n! Round\n! #\n! Player\n! Pos\n! Nationality\n! College/Junior/Club Team (League)\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|29<sup>1</sup>\n| [[Rasmus Sandin]]\n| D\n| {{flagicon|SWE}} Sweden\n| [[Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds]] ([[Ontario Hockey League|OHL]])\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|52<sup>2</sup>\n| [[Sean Durzi]]\n| D\n| {{flagicon|Canada}} Canada\n| [[Owen Sound Attack]] (OHL)\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|76<sup>3</sup>\n| [[Semyon Der-Arguchintsev]]\n| C\n| {{flagicon|Russia}} Russia\n| [[Peterborough Petes]] (OHL)\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|83<sup>4</sup>\n| [[Riley Stotts]]\n| C\n| {{flagicon|Canada}} Canada\n| [[Calgary Hitmen]] ([[Western Hockey League|WHL]])\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|4\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|118\n| [[Mac Hollowell]]\n| D\n| {{flagicon|Canada}} Canada\n| [[Sault Ste. Marie Greyhounds]] (OHL)\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|149\n| [[Filip Kr\u00e1l|Filip Kral]]\n| D\n| {{flagicon|Czech Republic}} Czech Republic\n| [[Spokane Chiefs]] (WHL)\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|156<sup>5</sup>\n| [[Pontus Holmberg]]\n| RW\n| {{flagicon|Sweden}} Sweden\n| [[VIK V\u00e4ster\u00e5s HK]] ([[Hockeyettan]])\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|7\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|209<sup>6</sup>\n| [[Zachary Bouthillier]]\n| G\n| {{flagicon|Canada}} Canada\n| [[Chicoutimi Saguen\u00e9ens]] ([[Quebec Major Junior Hockey League|QMJHL]])\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|7\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|211\n| [[Semyon Kizimov]]\n| RW\n| {{flagicon|Russia}} Russia\n| [[HC Ladia Togliatti|Ladia Togliatti]] ([[Junior Hockey League (Russia)|MHL]])\n|}\n'''Notes:'''\n# The [[Winnipeg Jets]]' first-round pick went to the Toronto Maple Leafs as the result of a trade on June 22, 2018, that sent a first-round pick in 2018 (25th overall) to St. Louis in exchange for a third-round pick in 2018 (76th overall) and this pick.<ref name=\"Bluesup4withLeafs\">{{cite web|title=Leafs select D Sandin with No. 29 pick|ur